data.chText: 拿不定主意；不确定；怀疑
data.enText: not sure; uncertain and feeling doubt

data.chText: 罗斯对整个设想持怀疑态度。
data.enText: Rose was doubtful about the whole idea.

data.chText: 他拿不定主意是否接受额外工作。
data.enText: He was doubtful about accepting extra work.

data.chText: 这未必就是毕加索的画。
data.enText: It's doubtful if this painting is a Picasso.

data.chText: 她多处受伤，今后能否行走还很难说。
data.enText: With her injuries it's doubtful that she'll ever walk again.

data.chText: 这辆汽车未必还能用上一年。
data.enText: It's doubtful whether the car will last another year.

data.chText: 他受了伤，明天未必能参赛。
data.enText: He is injured and is doubtful for the game tomorrow (= unlikely to play) .

data.chText: 不明朗；悬而未定；可能变糟
data.enText: uncertain and likely to get worse

data.chText: 战争刚开始时，形势看上去很不明朗。
data.enText: At the beginning of the war things were looking very doubtful.

data.chText: 低劣的；未必是真的；靠不住的
data.enText: of low value; probably not genuine or of a quality that you can rely on
This wine is of doubtful quality.

simple_means.memory_skill: doubt 怀疑 + ful 有…的 → 可疑的

example: they were doubtful that the cord would hold
it was doubtful whether she would be admitted
he has a dubious record indeed
what one found uncertain the other found dubious or downright false
it was more than dubitable whether the friend was as influential as she thought"- Karen Horne

value.def: If it is doubtful that something will happen, it seems unlikely to happen or you are uncertain whether it will happen.

example.ex: For a time it seemed doubtful that he would move at all...
example.tran: 有一段时间他似乎根本不会搬家。

example.ex: It is doubtful whether Tweed, even with his fluent French, passed for one of the locals...
example.tran: 尽管特威德能说一口流利的法语，他是否能被当作当地人还很难说。

example.ex: Whether the authorities will allow inspection is highly doubtful.
example.tran: 当局是否允许检查还是个大问号。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft <l>it</l> v-link ADJ that/wh

value.def: If you are doubtful about something, you feel unsure or uncertain about it.

example.ex: I was still very doubtful about the chances for success...
example.tran: 我对能否成功仍然深表怀疑。

example.ex: Why did he sound so doubtful?
example.tran: 为什么他听上去如此不确定？

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>about</l> n

value.tran: 怀疑的;疑惑的;拿不定主意的

value.def: If you say that something is of doubtful quality or value, you mean that it is of low quality or value.

example.ex: ...selling something that is overpriced or of doubtful quality...
example.tran: 售卖漫天要价或质量低劣的东西

example.ex: They also seemed of very doubtful value.
example.tran: 它们好像也没有多大价值。

example.ex: ...information that he described as having doubtful reliability.
example.tran: 据他所称未必可靠的消息

value.def: If a sports player is doubtful for a match or event, he or she seems unlikely to play, usually because of injury.

example.ex: Forsyth is doubtful for tonight's game with a badly bruised leg.
example.tran: 福赛斯腿部严重擦伤，不大可能参加今晚的比赛。

value.tran: (通常指运动员因伤)不大可能参加（比赛）的

value.boxu_tran: 不要混淆 doubtful, dubious, suspicious。doubtful 指不确定某事或不确定其是否会发生或成功：Do you feel insecure and doubtful about your ability（你对自己的能力缺乏信心，抱有怀疑吗），It was doubtful he would ever see her again（他会不会再见到她还说不准）。dubious 指拿不准做某事是否正确：Alison sounded very dubious（艾利森听上去犹豫不决），The men in charge were a bit dubious about taking women on（几位男性负责人有点儿拿不准要不要招女员工）。dubious 还可指某事物不完全可信、安全或可靠：his dubious abilities as a teacher（他的教学能力令人怀疑）。suspicious 指不信任某人，怀疑其从事欺骗性或不法活动：I am suspicious of his intentions（我怀疑他动机不纯），Miss Lenaut had grown suspicious（莱诺小姐已经起了疑心）。suspicious 还可指某人的行为可疑、不诚实、涉及非法或具有危险性：He listened for any suspicious sounds（他注意倾听任何可疑的声音），in suspicious circumstances（在可疑的情势下）。
value.boxu_usage: Do not confuse doubtful, dubious, and suspicious. If you feel doubtful about something, you are unsure about it or about whether it will happen or be successful. Do you feel insecure and doubtful about your ability?... It was doubtful he would ever see her again. If you are dubious about something, you are not sure whether it is the right thing to do. Alison sounded very dubious... The men in charge were a bit dubious about taking women on. If you describe something as dubious, you think it is not completely honest, safe, or reliable. ...his dubious abilities as a teacher. If you are suspicious of a person, you do not trust them and think they might be involved in something dishonest or illegal. I am suspicious of his intentions... Miss Lenaut had grown suspicious. If you describe something as suspicious, it suggests behaviour that is dishonest, illegal, or dangerous. He listened for any suspicious sounds. ...in suspicious circumstances.
